&lt;p>This is your starting point for learning Python as a powerful tool for data analytics. Whether you are new to programming or already have some experience, this course and its lessons will help you understand how Python can assist in exploring and understanding data.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Lesson 2 - Variables and Data Types</title><link>/docs/python/python-basics/lesson-2-variables-and-data-types/</link><pubDate>Thu, 07 Sep 2023 16:04:48 +0200</pubDate><guid>/docs/python/python-basics/lesson-2-variables-and-data-types/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="building-on-your-knowledge-of-python-data-handling">Building on Your Knowledge of Python Data Handling&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>In this lesson, we’ll learn how to store values and work with both numerical and text data in Python. Knowing how to manage numbers and strings sets the groundwork for more advanced tasks, including data analytics and machine learning models. Before starting, it’s best if you already know how to write basic Python code and perform simple arithmetic operations.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Lesson 3 - Lists and For Loops</title><link>/docs/python/python-basics/lesson-3-lists-and-for-loops/</link><pubDate>Sat, 07 Dec 2024 16:04:48 +0200</pubDate><guid>/docs/python/python-basics/lesson-3-lists-and-for-loops/</guid><description>This lesson introduces lists, indexing, slicing, and for loops in Python, and shows how to read and process a large dataset efficiently.</description></item><item><title>Lesson 4 - Introduction to Python</title><link>/docs/python/python-basics/lesson-4-introduction-to-python/</link><pubDate>Thu, 07 Sep 2023 16:07:48 +0200</pubDate><guid>/docs/python/python-basics/lesson-4-introduction-to-python/</guid><description>&lt;svg
